{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "(CH1) They satisfy an indistinguishability condition in the interchange of the indices i ↔ j and h ↔ k, namelyB hk ij (g, cos θ) = B kh ji (g, cos θ), ∀v, v * ∈ R 3, ∀θ ∈ [0, π].",
    "(CH2) They decompose into the product of a kinetic part Φ hk ij ≥ 0 and an angular part b hk ij ≥ 0, namelyB hk ij (g, cos θ) = Φ hk ij (g)b hk ij (cos θ), ∀v, v * ∈ R 3, ∀θ ∈ [0, π].",
    "(CH3)The kinetic part has the form of reactive Maxwellian or hard-potential interactions, i.e.for any γ ∈ [0, 1],Φ hk ij (g) = C hk ij g hk ij γ+1 2 g 1-γ 2, C hk ij > 0, C hk ij m 2 ij = C ij hk m 2 hk, ∀v, v * ∈ R 3.",
    "(CH4) The angular part is assumed to be positive for a.e.",
    "θ ∈ [0, π] and to satisfy the condition b hk ij (cos θ) = b ij hk (cos θ)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "(CH3)The kinetic part has the form of reactive Maxwellian or hard-potential interactions, i.e.for any γ ∈ [0, 1],Φ hk ij (g) = C hk ij g hk ij γ+1 2 g 1-γ 2, C hk ij > 0, C hk ij m 2 ij = C ij hk m 2 hk, ∀v, v * ∈ R 3."
  ]
}